<TITLE> Saarc countries meet on women, children </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 30 (bdnews24.com) - The South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation technical committee on women, youth and children began its second meeting in the city Monday. Secretary of the Ministry of Women and Children Affairs Rokeya Sultana inaugurated the two-day meeting being attended by representatives of all the Saarc countries. The meeting will evaluate the progress in implementation of various decisions taken by the higher Saarc bodies. Bangladesh is the current chair of the meeting. In her opening speech, the secretary said that it was obviously a reason for satisfaction that Bangladesh convened the meeting with a number of innovative solutions in addressing many social challenges of the country. She suggested considering engaging non-governmental organisations or the civil society stakeholders in its deliberations in the future. The meeting formally launched "A Primer on gender initiatives in SAARC" jointly published by Saarc and the United Nations Fund for Women to bring together innovative practices of gender mainstreaming and potential of such practices in the region. The committee will identify possible regional projects with focus on addressing issues relating to women and children. It will also evaluate the progress by respective countries in realising various goals of the Saarc Decade on Rights of the Child that spans from 2001 to 2010. bd
